EditorData.logicalname: Gortash Stone was picked up before.

Text.Value: Boo knows many gods. You don't look like any of them.
With your bones rotting beneath your father's hall - your name remembered by none.
None shall stand in my way.
You don't understand. I'm not an evil person.
Cowards! You waited until I did all the dirty work.
Out of my way! You look upon a god.
And you could have embraced death with a smile. Few are given such a choice.
Jaheira hoped there was still some flimsy light of good within you, small as Boo but just as bright.
I care not.
We have slain queens. And gods. And one time, a giant. But never before a friend.
We have slain kings. And gods. And one time, a giant. But never before a friend.
I tried once before... but it seems Bhaal has too tight a grasp on you.
Live with it, if you can - I will not.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, barely restrained disgust - leaves after.

Text.Value: No more threats? I admit, I was hoping for -
But I won't give up on you - not just yet. I'm my own worst enemy in that regard.
Jaheira... what are you doing?
Boo and Minsc promise to make it swift, evil.
You can hear him, can't you? The Lord of Murder. You can hear, but you won't listen. I know you won't.
Drop that stone. You will want your hands free for what comes next.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player holding Nether stone/Dagger prop from Orin

Text.Value: There is nothing more to be said, but a final goodbye.
Withdraw undetected.
You have what you wanted, Chosen. And now you will see exactly what that means.
Congratulating you, of course.
I thought I'd saved you from Bhaal's clutches. Seems I failed, damn it all.
All is nothing to me, beside Father.
Jaheira... must it truly be this way?

EditorData.NodeContext: Minsc almost sobbing, he is very erluctant

Text.Value: But if she hasn't... well, we'll mourn her later. She gave us a job to do.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim formality. He's there as a backup plan of Jaheira's in case we went rabid - and the fact that she's not with us is proof enough she's dead, and he has to fight us.

Text.Value: No... Please...
The Lord of Murder calls you. You know what your answer must be.
*Another part of your glimmering birthright, for you to abuse as you please.*
Greetings, Bhaalspawn. I hoped to see the High Harper walk out those doors with you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim formality. He's there as a backup plan of Jaheira's in case we went rabid - and the fact that she's not with us is proof enough she's dead, and he has to fight us.

Text.Value: Still though, I won't leave. There's a good person in there somewhere.
Bhaal below, I thought I got rid of you.
I tried to wrest you from Bhaal's grip once already. Seems I failed.
And I stand beside you now. I know you. You're more than this. More than Bhaal. You're my friend, and I won't leave you.
I tried to save you - when Bhaal came for you before, I stood by you.
Then you've made your choice.

EditorData.NodeContext: Utter fury, all the worse because she's keeping it restrained.

Text.Value: Bhaal was going to kill me if I didn't accept!
I don't want you to die. I want you to serve.
Think carefully. Do not give yourself to the Dread Lord, no matter how strong your cravings.
*The stone trembles with evils, warm as Father's hate.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player holding Nether stone/Dagger prop from Orin
EditorData.logicalname: NO MINSC OR JAHEIRA OR FLOW AFTER THEY LEFT

Text.Value: *You feel a tug of recognition - Minsc's unwitting mind, mingled tides of anger, grief, confusion. Friends and enemies, melding beyond recognition.*
I shall use the stone well, I promise.
This stone gives control over the Absolute. It must be mine.
But... but this? I can't pardon this. I can't fix this. This is it. It's over.
I really hoped we could avoid being pawns for a dark god, but here we are, I suppose.
Let's not fight, I didn't want any of this.

EditorData.logicalname: NO MINSC OR JAHEIRA AND HAS GORTASH STONE

Text.Value: *Unease fills the Bhaal Temple's stagnant air.*
I'm with you, my dear. Wherever this leads.
I know better. I stood here a century ago, and watched this same ceremony unfold. I stand here again to show you how it ends:
Boo and I - we once hoped that that was true. But no longer.
You have won Bhaal's bloody blessing. Now you think you will step out into the world, and carve your name upon it.
And Minsc shall be your undoing!
Harpers - let us do what we must.

EditorData.NodeContext: Authorative order to the Harpers she's gathered - to kill the party.

Text.Value: You really think you can kill me? ME? The Slayer-Queen!
You really think you can kill me? ME? The Slayer-King!
I will mourn the person you were. But I will not accept the one you've become.
Do not look, Boo. It is no longer our friend who stands there.

EditorData.NodeContext: Genuinely broken-hearted that we accepted Bhaal (leaves with Jaheira, to ambush us outside)

Text.Value: Ease his confusion. Try to control him.
Without you, there would be no Absolute. This was all your doing.
Of course, I didn't mean a word I said to Bhaal.
What about you? Will you protect the world from what he has become?
What about you? Will you protect the world from what she has become?
What about you? Will you protect the world from what they have become?
AAAAAAAARRRRGGGGGH!
We should all begin to pray.
*A simple command. Your tadpole provides the means, your bloodline the message: to end these petty mortals who plague your Father.*
Damn you. I cannot turn my back. I will not.
You can lie to Minsc. Perhaps even to Jaheira. But not to Boo.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sadly - he'll fight us to the death but he didn't want it to come to this

Text.Value: What did I - ? What did you make Minsc do?!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A rasp of steel, and Jaheira stops short with a wet gasp - then falls forward, revealing Minsc holding his bloodied sword. The mind-meld dissipates, and he looks at her body with growing horror. Then to us, rage and grief building.

Text.Value: You've chosen the company you keep - I will not allow the Bhaalspawn to hide behind you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, ready to kill us - not apologetic, but explaining that we've brought this on ourselves.

Text.Value: Let's end this talk.
Careful what you do with that thing...
He calls to you, doesn't he? Bhaal. Resist him - to rule in his name would be to lose who you truly are.
Only a respite. Do not forget who knows the Bhaalspawn better than any alive. Your path only ever led one way.
Goodbye, Bhaalspawn. Harpers, to arms. Let's defend this city as we always have.
This path was not of our choosing, Minsc. But we must walk it all the same.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gentle, but resolute - Minsc doesn't want to kill us and Jaheira understands, but she knows we're too far gone

Text.Value: I tried to save you from the Lord of Murder - and still you gave in.
I really hope you know what you're doing.
Boo and I - we prayed it would be Orin who prevailed. It would make the slaughter to come a little gentler.
Minsc and I, we know better. We stood here a century ago, and watched this same ceremony unfold. We stand here again to show you how it ends:
Fall in line. We leave, now.
Then I am afraid you don't know us at all - as we never truly knew you.
Yours are not the hands in which I would have placed such terrible power. Think carefully on your next action, please.
Who is this performance for, Bhaalspawn? It is only us here - you need not pretend.

Synopsis:
The Dark Urge accepted Bhaal when he appeared. Now, Jaheira and Minsc challenge and try to take down the DU, if they were encountered and survived until this point in the game.
If the Jaheira/Minsc scene cannot trigger, there will be fallback comments from the party.
